This is a Cursor-specific overlay. **Canonical source: [`rules/core/architecture.md`](../../rules/core/architecture.md).**

## Module boundaries — non-negotiable

- Modules **NEVER** import from other modules.
- `app/platform/*` MUST NOT import `app/modules/*`.
- `app/components/*` should remain domain-agnostic and SHOULD NOT import `app/modules/*`.

## Allowed imports from within a module

Relative imports within the same module subtree, plus:

- `app/components/*` (shared UI)
- `app/hooks/*` (generic UI hooks only)
- `app/utils/*` (generic utilities only)
- `app/platform/*` (infrastructure)
- `app/layout/*` (app shell — can import from modules for shell integration)
- `@commerce-atoms/*` (pure logic packages)

## Cross-module reuse ladder

1. Duplicate intentionally (< 50 lines).
2. Promote to `app/components/**` (`primitives/`, `catalog/`, `commerce/`, `pagination/`).
3. Promote to `app/hooks/*`.
4. Promote to `app/utils/*`.
5. Extract pure logic to `@commerce-atoms/*`.
6. Create platform utilities.

## Forbidden dumping-ground folders

`app/lib`, `app/common`, `app/shared`, `app/ui`.

## Route / view separation

- `*.route.tsx` owns loaders / actions / meta / headers / Storefront API calls.
- `*.view.tsx` owns rendering only — no API calls, no sessions, no meta exports.

## No barrel files

Never create `index.ts` exports. Always use explicit imports.
